Another length ball and outside off, Labuschagne defends it off his front foot.
Labuschagne defends this length ball outside off towards the off side off the full face of the bat.
Archer goes down leg and Labuschagne fails to lay bat on ball as the ball takes the pad towards fine leg and the batsman cross for a leg bye.
On a length but the line is way down the leg side. Head goes for a flick but fails to connect.
Labuschagne defends this length ball from Woakes towards the off side.
Labuschagne flicks this length ball from woakes towards mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
On a Length and outside off Head stands tall defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery outside off from Woakes, Head drives it to find the fielder at mid off.
Length ball but going down the leg, Head looks to flick but takes a blow on his thigh pad.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! Head stands tall on this length ball and drives it straight down the ground towards the long on fence for a boundary.
Archer goes short and Labuschagne pulls it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and around off, Head looks to drive it but gets it off the outside half of his bat to covers.
Length ball outside off, Head does a sensible thing of not playing the ball outside off.
Head once again leaves the length ball outside off, only for the keeper to take it above his head.
On a length and around off, Head comes right behind the line of the delivery to defend that.
Archer loses his line as he sprays one down leg and Head goes after it looking to flick it only to miss it.
A length ball wide outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Beaten! Wasn't there a nick? Apparently no. Full and outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Someone appeals but no conviction.
WIDE. Miles outside the off stump, outside the pitch, left alone. Collected in front of first slip by Bairstow.
On a length and around off, Labuschagne defends it towards the off side with soft hands.
Length ball and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Broad bowls one on the length but he is no way near to making the batsman play and Labuschagne is happy to leave it.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne is aware off his front foot and cooly shoulders arms to it.
Length delivery outside off, Head taps it to covers for a single.
Short pitch stuff from Archer, Labuschagne drops his wrists to sway away from the line of the delivery.
Another bouncer and Labuschagne is happy to drop his wrists once again and get out of the line of fire.
Archer has gone back to bowling short stuff, Labuschagne looks least interested to even play at it.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball go with out even fending with it.
Labuschagne is happy to shoulder arms to this length ball outside off from Archer.
On a length and around off, Head flicks it through mid-wicket and takes a single.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne is in no mood to play the wide one here. He leave one for the keeper.
Another length ball and another leave from Marnus. Great composure by the young lad here.
Labuschagne drives this length ball through covers and crosses over to the other end.
A swinging length ball on the stumps, Head plays a strong front foot defense.
FOUR! Length ball and outside off, Head drives it crisply through covers and the ball crosses the fence in a flash.
Length ball but the line is down leg and Labuschagne does what he has done till now, leave it.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne hops and defends it to the leg side.
Length delivery on the pads, Labuschagne defends towards the leg side and luckily for him, the ball bounces just in front of short leg as the ball was in the air for quite some time.
No Ball! Jofra oversteps. He bowls one on a length and goes one down the leg side. Labuschagne looks to flick but fails to connect it.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot to the off side.
Second No ball in the over. Archer again oversteps. He bowls one on a length and outside off, Labuschagne defends it off his back foot towards the off side.
FOUR! This time Labuschagne doesn't miss the flick. Archer bowls one on back of a length and on the pads and Labuschagne flicks it off his pads through fine leg for a boundary.
On a length and down leg and Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball outside off, punched straight to cover.
Full and around off, driven straight back to the bowler.
FOUR! PRISTINE! Full and outside off, Head leans and drives it through the covers. No soul moves.
A length ball, around off, angling in, tucked straight to short mid-wicket.
A length ball, around middle, Travis gets across and helps it towards square leg.
Outside off, left alone watchfully.
Tossed up delivery on the stumps, Labuschagne drives it to covers.
Tossed up around off, Labuschagne works it towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Tossed up delivery on the pads, Head works it around the corner for a single.
Around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, worked through square leg for a run.
Full and outside off, driven straight back to the bowler.
A short ball outside off, punched towards cover.

Length ball outside off, Head looks to tap it through point but gets soft leading edge which falls just short of Ben Stokes at third slip. He certainly saved a boundary for his team. Joe Denly from backward point does the cleaning act as the batsmen cross for a single.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne once again decides not to play at it. He is aware that Tea is around the corner here.
Archer bowls on a length and outside off and once again Labuschagne is happy to play the leaving game here.
Last ball of the session and Labuschagne shoulders arms to this length delivery outside off form Archer. And that's TEA ON DAY 2! Australia are 82/3!
Sharp spin from the rough outside off, the length is on the shorter side and Head works it to square leg. He wants a run but his partner turns it down.
A low full toss on off, Travis lunges and pushes it down towards mid on.

Almost drags it on! Full and flighted outside off, spinning back in, Head attempts to drive against the turn but only manages to inside edge it onto his pads. Poor technique, if you want to play that shot, you need to get entirely forward to smother the spin.
Flatter and shorter on off, Head rocks back and slaps it square of the wicket on the off side. Burns chases it down from point and they take three runs.
A bit short and on off, played down from the crease to point.
Shortish and close to off, Marnus plays a mistimed back foot punch to covers.

Fantastic delivery first up. Stokes wastes no time in warming up. He is right on the money with a well-directed bouncer. Head is caught in a tangle as he takes his eyes off the ball. Tries to move away but fails and then somehow fends it off towards square leg.
The line is straighter and Head has helped it off his pads to the leg side.

Peach of a delivery! Stokes lands it on a shorter length close to middle and gets it to jag back in sharply. Head waits on the back foot to deal with it but is beaten for extra bounce. Takes a blow on his stomach. Must have hurt but he isn't showing much.
A bit short and on off, Head punches from the back foot but finds the cover fielder.
Serves one on the pads, Head tries his best to flick but misses.
In the corridor of uncertainty, Head lets the ball go outside his off stump. Maiden to start for Ben!
Flighted ball, full and just around off, Marnus leans forward and defends it right under his watchful eyes.
Lovely footwork. He is so smooth on his feet. Apt replacement for Steven Smith. He comes down the track for a fuller delivery and drives it through covers for a run.
Full and on off, it's driven through the line but straight to the fielder at extra cover.
Spinning back into the batsman from around off, Head clips it with the spin but finds mid-wicket.
On the pads, eased behind square leg for one.
Loopy and landing full on off, Labuschagne is watchful in his forward defense. The scorecard reads 87/3, the devil's number for Australia.
Brave, very brave! Head trusted the bounce there and left it alone. Good length ball close to off, it straightened a bit and Head offered no shot.
Lead touches 200! Angling down the leg side, Head nudges it down to fine leg for one.

ROOT DROPS! Dear me, he is having a tough time! Back-to-back ducks and now a catch going down. Poor Stokes. He deserved a wicket. Lovely delivery. A touch short and around off, some late movement, Labuschagne sticks back to poke inside the line and gets a big outside edge behind at first slip. Root fails to grab it in his first attempt near his waist with a jump, tries again on the rebound but it doesn't stick and falls down.
Fullish and on off, Marnus defends it off his front foot towards mid off.
Leans forward to a full ball and drives it in the direction of mid off.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump. Good over by Stokes, deserved a wicket but the catch went down.
Beaten! Quicker through the air, short and outside off, Head attempts to cut but misses.
Walks forward to a full ball and eases it with the spin to mid on.
Once again Head uses footwork and pushes it down on the leg side.
Full and flighted on off, Head strokes it off his front foot to mid off.
Short and outside off, it's cut square of the wicket on the off side for a run.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. Leach tosses this one in the air and lands it full around off, Labuschagne skips down the track and tries to play it near his front pad. The English players appeal thinking it's pad first but the umpire stays put. Root asks his teammates regarding the usage of the DRS but he's not getting any convincing answer. The time lapses. The replays are shown after that. It confirms that the ball struck Marnus first on the pads but the impact is an issue. Later on, it shows the ball to be hitting the off stump. Interesting. It looked like spinning away but the ball just skidded through the line on the Ball Tracker. Hmm...
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Outside off, pushed through point for a single.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a couple.
A bouncer outside off, Marnus ducks.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball outside off, coming in a long way, ML gets out of harm's way. That does not miss the off stump by much.
Advances down the track and then allows the ball to spin back in from outside off. Head, then, gently pushes it out towards cover-point.
Full and around off, turning in, Head tries another flawed drive again the spin and gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Good half-stop by Broad! Loopy and full on off, Head shimmies down the track and drives it down the ground towards mid off. Broad dives across to his left to take the pace off the ball. The batsmen complete the single as the mid on fielder mops up. Was Stuart faking a throw there? Not sure. But if he did, that's against the new rules.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated one on middle, Labuschagne tries playing straight but it skids on to take the inside edge. Rolls safely to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Shot! Flighted delivery around off, Labuschagne dances down the track and powers it over Broad at mid on for a boundary.
Shortish and outside off, Head reaches out for it and plays it down towards cover-point.

OUT! Corker of a yorker and Head is a goner! Stokes has been bowling brilliantly in his first spell. One catch went down off his bowling but he didn't lose hope. Delivers a pinpoint yorker with good pace, right in the line of the stumps, Head brings his bat down to dig it out but it takes the inside edge and rattles the stumps. Looking at the replays, had his bat not come down in time, it would have missed the off stick. Bad luck in a way for the batter. The 45-run stand is broken and England would like to make use of this opening. The lead is 209 at the moment.
Back of a length delivery in the zone outside off, Wade makes a safe leave.
Yet another delivery in the channel of apprehension, Wade is very watchful while making another leave.
Stokes persists with his line on and around off and gets it to leave the left-hander. Wade feels for it a bit and gets beaten.
On middle and leg this time, Wade works it off his pads to mid-wicket. A wicket maiden for Stokes.
Loopy and full on off, Labuschagne is on the front foot in defense.
Skidding into the batsman from around middle, Marnus moves back and works it in front of square leg for a run.
Quicker through the air, outside off, Wade shuffles across the stumps and then blocks it back.

FOUR! Poor piece of fielding in the deep by Denly. Floated full around off, Wade kneels down and sweeps it through backward square leg. Denly near the fence makes a complete mess and Wade opens his account with a boundary. 100 comes up for Australia as well.

Aerial but just over the keeper! Loopy ball around off, turning back in, Wade tries to repeat the last shot but this one climbs onto his bat and catches the top edge. It flies over Bairstow and the first slip fielder runs after it. He pulls it back before the fence and the batsmen take a brace.
Works it with the spin to the leg side but finds the mid-wicket fielder. 7 from the over after a wicket maiden!
Angling down the leg side, it's nudged to fine leg for one.
Full in length around off, Wade with an open stance defends it back to the bowler.
Slants across a length delivery outside off, Wade allows it through to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery down the leg side, Matthew tries to tickle it fine but fails to get any wood behind it.
Fractionally short in length and around off, Wade picks the length early, leans back, drops his wrists, keeps his eyes on the ball and watches it till the ball disappears in Bairstow's gloves.
FOUR! Fine timing! Stokes is too straight with his line and the length is very full as well, Wade leans forward and clips it beautifully through mid-wicket.
Full and flighted on off, Marnus uses his feet and drives it towards mid off.
Loopy and full on middle, Labuschagne lunges and defends it back.
Tossed up ball on off, a touch short in length, Marnus gets back and punches it to sweeper cover for a run.
Flatter and shorter outside off, turning back in, Wade hangs on the back foot and strokes it to sweeper cover for one.
Hurls this delivery in the flatter trajectory, around off, Labuschagne is back in defense.
Nicely floated delivery, full and on off, ML prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Digs in a short ball on middle and off, Wade arches back, drops his wrists and sways away from the line of fire.
Bouncer down the leg side, Wade ducks at the last moment.
Stokes bangs it in again, Wade takes his eyes off it and lets it go over his head as he bends.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Wade stands tall inside the crease and defends it back.
Stokes bowls a half-tracker again. It's on middle and Wade moves away safely. Maiden.
Loopy delivery, landing full on off, Labuschagne drives it past the diving cover fielder to mid off.
Full and floated on off, driven off the front foot to covers.
Tossed up ball around off, Labuschagne gets down on one knee and paddles it to fine leg for one.
Well played! Loopy and full outside off, Wade goes down and across before sweeping it wide of backward short leg. There is a fine leg present and hence a couple of runs.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

NOT OUT! It's umpire's call. Leach delivers a full ball on the rough outside off and gets it to break back into the batsman. Wade is on the back foot when he should have been forward. Tries to work it around but is beaten for spin and bounce. The ball strikes Wade on the right thigh and they appeal. The umpire shakes his head and there is a delayed call by Root to take the DRS. The Ball Tracker finds that it's clipping the leg stump. Review is retained though.
Bouncer! The batsman does well to evade it.

SAFE! Good length ball on middle and leg, sliding down with some extra bounce, Labuschagne tries to work it on the leg side but fails to middle his shot properly. There is some sound as it goes past Marnus and Bairstow collects the ball with a full length dive to his left. They appeal and the finger goes up quickly. Marnus wastes no time in signalling for the DRS and the Ultra Edge confirms that there was no bat. Decision overruled.
On middle and leg, played off the pads to mid-wicket.
Bumper! Stokes just trying to push the batsman on the back foot. Labuschagne ducks.
Brilliant delivery. It's on a length outside off, shaping away, Marnus pushes inside the line with a tentative footwork and gets beaten.
This time it's a big inswinger. Back of a length and outside off, Labuschagne attempts to defend from the crease but it whizzes past the outside edge of his bat. Top over, a maiden!
Loopy and full on off, Wade advances down the track and helps it with the spin to square leg.

FOUR! Boom! Leach serves a half-tracker on off, Wade goes deep inside the crease and pulls it with the spin to the deep mid-wicket fence. Bring the batsman forward is the advice from the keeper to the bowler.

FOUR! Wade is on the attack! Bairstow's advice Leach follows. But Wade has also heard it. He premeditates his charge down the track, takes it on the full and slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary. The Aussie keeper (who isn't keeping at the moment) is looking good now.
Tossed up ball landing outside off and spinning back in, Wade tries to defend but misses. He is hit on the pads but the point of impact is well outside off.
Fuller and on middle, Wade runs down the track and eases it to mid on for one.
Marnus strokes a full ball towards wide mid off for one. 10 from the over, a good one for Australia. Lead is now 14 short of 250!
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks it with the angle of the bowler to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Effort delivery but direction-less. Back of a length delivery sliding down the leg side, Marnus shoulders arms and watches it go down to the keeper.
Another delivery going down the leg side and it has been left alone. Stokes is working on a plan, it seems. There is a leg gully in place at the moment as well.
Fractionally short and outside off, Labuschagne goes on his toes and taps it down to point.
Another effort delivery and this time Stokes has overstepped. Shortish and outside off, Marnus lets it through to the keeper.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Lands it on a length around middle and skidding down, Labuschagne fails to flick and it goes off his pads to square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Starts his new spell with a good length delivery outside off, Marnus watches the line closely before making a leave.
FOUR! Gorgeous! Plenty of width on offer outside off, it's on a length, Labuschagne reaches out for it and drives it a bit aerially but safely through covers for a boundary.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another watchful leave outside the off stump.
Loses his radar this time and serves it way down the leg side. The batsman lets it through and Bairstow dives across to his left to collect the ball.
Shortish and on middle, it's played down with soft hands to square leg for one.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne defends it to the off side.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne drives it straight to mid off.
Length ball outside off and Labuschagne lets the ball go through. And what are we seeing - ARCHER IS LIMPING! 'England are gone', says my colleague with a tongue-twisting name, Mrinal.
Stokes has overstepped once again. He bowls one on a length but the line is down the leg side. Labuschagne looks to flick but fails to lay wood on the ball.
Labuschagne flicks a length ball off his pads to mid-wicket for a run.
On a length and outside off, Wade has opted to leave the length ball outside off.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and down the leg side, Labuschagne tickles it towards fine leg for a couple.

Landed outside off, Labuschagne lets it go. The ball comes in a long way and hits him on the pads and England appeal but umpire Wilson shakes his head. They do not take the review. Ball Tracker shows it to be missing off stump.
Around off, solidly defended.

Another LBW appeal, turned down again. A length ball, down the leg side, Marnus gets across to flick but misses. The ball hits his pads and England appeal but this is going down leg again. A leg bye taken.
Outside off, left alone.

NO BALL. But had Labuschagne nicked it? Shane Warne reckons yes and Ultra Edge confirms! Another let-off for the South African-born. A length ball outside off, Labuschagne looked to defend but at the last moment, thought about taking his bat away. There was a noise as the ball went past and England appealed but the umpire shook his head. The hosts went for the review but they could not get the technology as the first replay itself showed that Stokes had overstepped.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A short ball, Marnus ducks.
A length ball outside off, a waft from Marnus but missed.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, this time Wade pushes and misses.
Woakes delivers it on a length close to off and gets it to move in a bit, Labuschagne helps it in front of square leg and crosses.
Back of a length ball outside off, angling away, Wade covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Fractionally short in length and outside off, Wade once again has nothing to do with it.
That's a peach. It's on a length close to off and leaves the batsman with the angle, Wade tries to defend by getting a bit forward but it beats the outside edge.
Woakes tries to repeat the last delivery from the middle and leg line, Wade eases it to the left of mid on and crosses for a run.
On a length and close to off, Marnus sticks on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
NO BALL. Another overstepping. Stokes is frustrated. Oversteps by a bigger margin (as compared to the Labuschagne caught behind chance) and his fourth in 10 overs. Outside off, left alone.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
One more leave outside off.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
A bouncer, but down the leg side, Matthew ducks.

Ouch. On the box. Or just around it. Wade shows no pain. Stokes is furious with himself that he cannot get that a centimetre low. A length ball outside off, Wade shoulders arms but the ball comes back in a long way and hits him somewhere around the groin.

Another appeal for a caught behind. Not out again, says Wilson. Outside off, Labuschagne looked to punch but the ball came in and went off something to the keeper. The British thought about the review but did not take it. 'Ultra Edge detects a spike!', yells my dear Nabu. He is excited till his mate tells him to relax, showing the spike coming when the ball hit the pad.
Outside off, played straight to point.
Outside off, a length ball outside off, Marnus looked to punch but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A full toss, a release ball, Labuschagne punches it through point. A few teapots boiling in the field, hands on hips and no Archer to turn to. 50-RUN STAND IS UP as well.
Outside off, left alone.
A short ball, pulled through square leg for a couple. The lead is now 261.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball outside off, Matthew initially ducks, then sways. Watches the ball swing away late towards the keeper.
Outside off, let through again.
Outside off again, another leave.

FOUR! A length ball around off, coming in, Wade gets across and looks to tickle and gets a bit of an inside edge onto his pads, towards fine leg. Chris Woakes runs across to his left, gets to the ball with a slide but then lets it through.
Outside off, quietly left alone.
Around off, defended solidly.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Works this through mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump. 50 overs bowled.
On and around off, Marnus has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
In the channel outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Back of a length ball on off, angling away from 'round the wicket, Labuschagne feels for it and gets beaten.

DROPPED! Second life for Marnus Labuschagne! Stokes delivers it on a length close to off, it shapes in a shade as Labuschagne is forward to defend. But it takes the outside edge and flies in the direction of first slip. Bairstow realizes that it won't carry to Root and hence he puts in a dive across to his right. Catches it with his right hand but it pops out of his glove as soon as his elbow hits the ground. Tough chance but at this level, they need to catch these. Marnus continues to ride his luck.
Watchful this time. In the zone outside off, Marnus has nothing to do with it.
Short ball on middle, pulled down fine on the leg side for one. Another luckless over for Ben comes to an end.
Full and outside off, Labuschagne drives it down the ground and the ball races away but Chris Woakes dives to his right and makes a terrific stop. Just a single.
Well wide outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone again.
Full and outside off, let through.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Landed outside off, driven towards Jofra Archer at mid off.
A bouncer but down the leg side, calmly ducked under.

That will test Archer's hamstring. Full and around middle, Labuschagne flicks it wide of mid on. Jofra Archer gives it a good chase from mid on to his right and stops the ball. Three runs taken. Had Labuschagne missed it, he would have been dead plumb LBW.
Outside off, left alone.

Almost a reminiscence of his first innings' dismissal! A terrific yorker, around middle, Matthew falls over and almost is late in getting his bat down. Luckily for him, the ball hits the bat and stops.
FOUR! Streaky. Full and outside off, Wade throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge which flies past a diving gully to third man!

OUT! Bounced out! Caught behind. Salute to you, O big Ben, O lion-hearted fellow. You have tried and tried and tried, not given up, kept coming at the batsmen and eventually, in a 13-over spell, struck. And he throws a salute to the fans. A brute of a bouncer, outside off, Wade ducks but the ball kicks up suddenly. Wade cannot do much and the ball flies off the glove to the keeper who leaps to collect. The English appeal but Wade does not even wait a second to go. End of a 66-run stand.
A short ball, swat-pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
Huge LBW shout, turned down. A length ball, outside off, coming in, Paine looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. Impact outside off.

OUT! CAUGHT! There is an inside edge. Big inside edge. But Paine shakes his head! Bizarre. A length ball, outside off, coming in again, Paine walks across to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. Now, England appeal and the umpire raises his finger! The slip cordon though, is busy looking at gully, where Joe Denly is coming running in to take the catch. Root is even more confident now and puts his entire strength in the appeal. Paine has a look at his partner, has a long discussion and then takes it upstairs. A bemused Root asks Paine why is he reviewing. Paine says he hit it. Then Root smiles and says that you are out caught! Shake of the head from the Aussie skipper. The third umpire is told by umpire Wilson that it is an LBW review. Dear me. Big inside edge, lobbing to gully. Umpire Wilson missed the nick. How on earth did Paine miss it? Waste of a review. Australia lose two quickly, bang bang. Effectively 276/6.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Stokes steams in and delivers a good length ball down the leg side, Marnus has a half-hearted attempt to flick and misses.
This one is on the pads, Labuschagne helps it to square leg for a run.
Angles in a full length ball on off, Pattinson defends it near his front pad.
Beauty by Big Ben! What an effort from him! A lovely outswinger, close to off and nipping away, Pattinson pushes inside the line minus any footwork and misses.
Another outswinger around off, this time James lets it be.
On a length and around off, this one heads towards the stumps after pitching, Pattinson defends it from the back foot.

Fifty for Marnus Labuschagne, third in a row! The first concussion substitute is turning out to be a super substitute for Australia. Short in length on off, Marnus pulls it off his front foot to deep mid-wicket for a couple. Another wonderful knock by him, he got a few lives this time but take nothing away from his application.
Shortish again and this time Marnus pulls it for a run at deep backward square leg.
This one is slanted into the batsman from 'round the wicket, James is forward in defense.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a length and outside off, Pattinson presses forward and confidently drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Spears in a full ball on middle and leg, Pattinson tries flicking but closes the face of the bat early. It goes off the leading edge and rolls back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, swinging in, Labuschagne falls over a touch and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Full and well outside off, could have been a wide but it is not signalled.
Half volley wide outside off, driven straight to short extra cover.
Guess Labuschagne is done for the day. A length ball, Marnus gets across and tucks it towards long leg for a single.
A length ball just outside off, Pattinson is tight in defense.
Nope. A dot ball. Pattinson survives. A length ball outside off, James shoulders arms. STUMPS ON DAY 2, AUSTRALIA EFFECTIVELY 283/6!
Begins his spell with a delivery on the driving length outside off, Labuschagne watches the line and then makes a leave.
This time it has been angled into the batsman, the length is quite full and it's clipped to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Switches his angle for the left-hander. Broad comes from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball in the zone outside off, Pattinson allows it through.
Angling in on middle and leg, a length ball, Pattinson defends it off his pads to the leg side.
Another delivery in the region outside off, Pattinson has nothing to do with it.
Broad puts it on a full length and just outside off, there to be driven but Pattinson is very watchful as he lets it go.
Good length ball landing outside off and angling in, Marnus gets behind the line and blocks it down safely.
Effort delivery on this occasion. Ben bends his back and digs in a short ball on off, it's easily left by Labuschagne.
A little bit of movement on this one. Full and outside off, Labuschagne drives off the front foot but finds the cover fielder.
Back of a length ball on off, shaping back in this time, Marnus moves back and taps it down in front of mid-wicket. Calls for a run and completes it with ease. Good running.
Pitches it up and close to off, this one holds its line just a bit, Pattinson covers his stumps and leaves. That wasn't too far away from the off pole.
Stokes pulls his length back a bit and delivers it outside off, James is not tempted into any kind of shot as he allows it through. It's been a cautious beginning from the Aussies.
Hint of inward movement. On a length around middle, Labuschagne tucks it in front of square leg for a single.
On and around off, a length ball, Pattinson is on the front foot in defense.

FOUR! Off the outside edge! Broad angles in a full ball on off, it heads towards the off stump after landing, Pattinson stays back to block it with soft hands but it takes the outside edge and speeds through the vacant gully region for a boundary.
Angles in a length ball on off, this time James has defended it from the middle of his bat.

Stifled appeal for an lbw! Broad lands it on a good length around middle and off, some extra bounce too. Pattinson tries to defend from the crease but misses and is hit high on the back leg. The replays suggest that there might have been a little bit of outside edge too.
Some width on offer outside off, Pattinson drives but finds the cover fielder.
Fractionally short in length and outside off, Labuschagne goes back to steer it square of the wicket on the off side but fails to beat the diving gully fielder.
Moving back into the batsman from outside off, Labuschagne goes inside the crease in defense.
An outswinger is hurled wide outside off, it's a comfortable leave for Marnus.
Stokes goes short but the line is outside off, Labuschagne crouches and sways away from the line.
Lands it on a length outside off, Labuschagne covers his stumps and allows it through to the keeper.
Shortish and on off, shaping away a bit, Marnus sticks on the back foot and taps it down towards backward point. First maiden of the morning!
Good length delivery in the region outside off, Pattinson is sticking to the plan of not taking any unnecessary chance. Calmly lets it be.
Broad gets straighter with his line this time, Pattinson just closes the face of his bat and helps it down to fine leg for one. The lead is now 9 away from 300!

Right-hand, left-hand combination always difficult to adjust. Broad comes from over the wicket for the righty but slips a length ball way down the leg side. Marnus leaves and Bairstow collects it with a dive to his left.

TOP EDGE! FOUR! Not in any control of the shot, Marnus. Broad bangs it in short on middle, Labuschagne takes the challenge of pulling it across the line but it takes the top edge and flies down safely to fine leg for a boundary. Stuart Broad tells the umpires that he has not hit it and this should have been leg byes. The decision is reversed to FOUR LEG BYES after the two umpires check it with Labuschagne!
Wild delivery. Way wide outside off, Labuschagne is in no mood to chase it.
Beauty by Broad. He angles in a length ball close to off, Marnus tries to defend by striding forward but it nips away just a bit to beat the outside edge.
Finally Pattinson runs out of patience. Short in length and wide outside off, James stands back, flashes his bat at it and misses.
Bouncer on middle, Pattinson easily sits underneath it.
Away swinger, landing on a length around off and moving away, Pattinson shoulders arms.
Fullish and on off, Pattinson gets his bat down and pushes it out safely to cover-point.
A lovely inswinging delivery, full and on off, Pattinson defends it back solidly.
Too much movement there. Stokes delivers it too straight and it moves down the leg side. James tries to keep it out but misses and is hit on the thigh pad. Another maiden from Ben!
Good length ball on off, shaping away, Labuschagne drives it behind square on the off side and looks for a run. He is sent back as Denly misses his shy at the striker's end.

FOUR! Glorious! In an attempt to get something extra from the surface, Broad overpitches around off. Labuschagne strides forward, shows the full face of the bat and drives it crisply past the left side of the mid off fielder.

DROPPED! Labuschagne gets yet another life. Broad screams in anguish, he cannot believe his luck. A lovely outswinger around off, Marnus tries driving through the line but it shapes away to take the outside edge. It goes to the right of Bairstow who flies in that direction but fails to hang on. The batsmen take two and Australia's lead crosses 300!
Short in length and on off, Marnus pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
On middle and leg, Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket and takes three runs. 11 runs and a dropped catch in the over!
Beaten! Labuschagne is a bit fidgety at the moment. Stokes delivers it on a length outside off and gets it to nip away, Labuschagne pushes inside the line and misses.

This time the shine is on the inside and the ball moves back in from a shortish length outside off. Labuschagne stays back to defend but it takes a thick inside edge and rolls behind square leg for one.
FOUR! Slapped away! Pattinson was holding himself back all this while but not this time. He gets width outside off and slaps it through point for a boundary.
Stokes tries to tempt the batsman once more. Puts it on a driving length outside off but Pattinson doesn't get carried away and watchfully makes a leave.
A wayward bouncer. Down the leg side, Pattinson doesn't bother even watching it as he allows it through.
200 up for Australia. On middle and leg, skidding in, Pattinson helps it through square leg for a run.
Fullish and on off, at a gentle pace, Pattinson pushes it out to mid off.
Fuller again, on middle, James helps it with soft hands towards mid-wicket and steals a quick run.
Driven towards the mid on region. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Shortish and sliding down the leg side, Pattinson fails to get any bat behind it.

FIVE RUNS! Not for the first time in this Test match, third five of the game. Slightly short in length and on middle, Pattinson helps it down towards mid-wicket and rushes for a quick run. Rory Burns has a shy at the bowler's end but misses as James dives in. The ball misses the stumps and there is no one backing up. It's a boundary.
Short and outside off, allowed to the keeper. 24 runs in the last three overs, Australia are scoring runs at a good rate now.
Beaten! A length ball on off, shaping away, James pushes inside the line and misses.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Fuller in length and on middle, Pattinson gets behind the line and defends it back solidly.

Nearly a drag on! Stokes serves a length ball in the line of the stumps, Pattinson tries to block it from the crease but it takes the inside edge, beats the stumps and runs down to fine leg for a run.
An outswinger outside off, landing on a good length, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Marnus gets across, crouches a bit and then lets it go behind to the keeper.

Miscommunication! Direct hit would have been curtains for Marnus Labuschagne. Shortish and on off, Pattinson dabs it down to the right of backward point and Labuschagne calls for a run. It's not there and suicidal. The fielder luckily for Marnus misses his shy at the striker's end.
Four byes! This one just shoots off the surface. Goes over the batsman and Jonny also fails to collect it with a jump.
Good length ball on middle, defended from the crease.
Straighter on middle, Marnus works it on the leg side for one. 50-run stand comes up!
Archer oversteps this time and bowls a bouncer. Pattinson ducks.
Lands it on middle, Pattinson defends it on the leg side.

OUT! England finally have a breakthrough they dearly wanted this morning. The lead has reached 327 now though. Archer speeds in from 'round the wicket and hurls in a length ball on off, Pattinson stays back to defend but it shapes away a bit and takes the outside edge. Root takes the catch safely at first slip. A valiant stand comes to an end.
Serves a length ball outside off, Labuschagne pushes at it and gets it away off the outside half of his bat towards point.
Sliding down the leg side, Marnus fails to flick and it goes behind off his pads. Bairstow fumbles and the batsmen take a leg bye.
FOUR! Soft hands! A length ball close to off stump, Cummins presents an angled bat to it, allows the ball to come to him. It takes the outer half and runs through gully.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Stays back and strokes it towards mid off.
Short delivery on middle, Pat helps it through square leg for a couple of runs. 7 from the over, the lead is worth 334 now.
Bowls a length delivery outside off, at 83 kph, Labuschagne allows it through and this one shoots up on its way to the keeper. A good take over his head by Jonny.

BANG ON THE HELMET! Archer steams in and digs in a well-directed bouncer, Labuschagne decides to make the leave but fails to take himself away from the line of fire. It smashes Marnus on the grille of the helmet and he goes down. Archer shows no sympathy and returns to his mark.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short in length and outside off, Labuschagne stays back patiently and then guides it over the slip cordon for a boundary.

Snorter! Archer once again bangs in a well-directed bouncer, Marnus is caught in an awkward position trying to fend it off. It takes the splice of his bat and loops up. There is no silly point in place and it falls down safely.
Back of a length ball on off, hitting 90 miles now, it's defended off the back foot to complete a hostile over.
In the region outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.

OUT! Caught at gully! Stokes hurls in a short ball around off, it jumps a bit onto the batsman, Cummins takes his eyes off the ball as he pushes at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and Rory Burns grabs a diving catch at gully. Nothing much offered in terms of batting by Pat. Maybe, those snorters from Archer in the previous over was playing in his mind and hence he got scared to watch a ball climbing onto him.
Good length ball outside off, shaping away, Lyon pokes inside the line and misses.
Beauty of a delivery, angling in around off and then shaping away, too good for a number 10 batsman. Lyon does his best but still fails to put bat on ball.
Stokes spears in a yorker this time, Lyon somehow digs it out safely.
Another play and a miss outside off by Lyon. End of a wicket maiden!

Labuschagne is rattled after facing a barrage of bouncers in Archer's last over. Back of a length ball around off, Marnus moves back inside the crease and tries to steer it through the line but misses.

FOUR! Nicely placed! Maybe, he was trying this shot on the last ball. Connects well. Short in length and outside off, Labuschagne stays back and ramps it down towards third man. There are two fielders behind square on the off side but he bisects them beautifully.
Interestingly takes a single and exposes Lyon to Archer. A length ball on middle is tucked through square leg for one.
Good length ball on middle and leg, angling down, Lyon tries flicking but misses. It goes behind off his pads, Bairstow only manages a half-stop and the batsmen take a leg bye.
Follows the batsman down the leg side with a bouncer, Marnus attempts to hook but misses.
Short in length and angling down the leg side again, Labuschagne moves across and tries to work it around but misses.

In the air... SAFE! Short in length on middle, Lyon tries to play the horizontal bat shot but fails to time it well. It flies over square leg and falls in no man's land. The fine leg fielder puts in a run and stops the ball. They cross for a couple of times.
Nipping away from the batsman outside off, Nathan pushes at it and misses.
Another beautiful outswinger by Ben, Lyon has no answer to that beauty. Tries to flirt with it but gets beaten.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Edgy! Stokes angles in a length ball on middle, straightening a bit after landing, Lyon tries to flick but gets a leading edge through covers for a couple.
Hurls a good length ball in the zone outside off, Nathan shoulders arms.
Spears in a length ball on middle at 89 mph, Marnus hops back to make space and then drives it to covers.
Smell the leather Labuschagne! Archer is after his head. Another rip-roaring bouncer, on middle, Marnus leans back and sways away from the line of fire.

OUT! Marnus Labuschagne is run out on 80 and he walks amidst a big ovation from the crowd. Archer offers width outside off, Marnus makes room and slaps it down to third man off the outer half. He runs the first run hard, turns for the second, wants it anyhow but before that a sharp and accurate throw from Denly comes to Bairstow and he breaks the stumps in a flash. Labuschagne is found short in the replays and the third umpire flashes OUT on the giant screen. The replays also showed that Denly had fumbled a bit before picking the ball but he managed to recover quickly.
Back of a length ball on off, Hazlewood defends it off his back foot.
FOUR! Lead crosses 350! Archer dishes out a sharp yorker on middle at 92 mph, Hazlewood gets his bat down in time and flicks it through mid-wicket.
Shortish and on middle, Hazlewood fails to move away from the line and takes a blow on his body. Another hostile over from Archer comes to an end.
Short and outside off, Lyon tries pulling but misses.
FOUR! Bad bounce for Woakes in the deep. Short delivery on middle, Lyon pulls it down to fine leg where Woakes kneels to stop it but the ball bounces extra and goes over him to meet the fence.
Inside edge. Sharp delivery, on a length around off and moving back in, Lyon winds up for a big heave across the line but inside edges it onto his pads.
Fullish and on off, Nathan bunts it down to mid off for a quick run.
Full and angling in on off, solidly blocked by Josh.
A yorker just outside off, too quick for the number 11 batsman. By the time he brings his bat down, the ball has gone past. Lucky for him, it wasn't in the line of the stumps.
Funny! Lyon gives the charge to Archer. He then forces a length ball down to mid on.

OUT! Lyon drags it on! Archer finishes things for England! A short delivery around off, at 90 mph, once again Lyon gives the charge and tries to flat-bat it through the line but gets a big inside edge onto the stumps. Australia are all out for 246, leading by 358 runs!
Pat Cummins begins from 'round the wicket and hurls in a short ball outside off, Burns crouches and allows it through.

Nearly a catch to short leg! Cummins darts in a length ball around off and gets it to move back in with some extra bounce. Burns tries to defend but it takes his gloves and lobs in front of short leg. It falls short of Wade there.
Cummins delivers it a touch short and outside off, gets it to move away, Burns keeps his bat close to his body and makes a leave.
Excellent delivery. This time Cummins has angled in a full length ball. It's closer to off this time, Burns is drawn forward in defense but the ball whistles past the outside edge.
Much better from Rory Burns. He watches the line closely which is wide outside off. Lifts his bat up and shoulders arms.
England's chase is underway! Cummins serves one on middle and leg, Rory clips it through square leg and returns for the second run.
Back of a length ball close to off, Roy remains on the back foot and taps it down to backward point.
Once again the length is a bit short and it angles into the batsman from around off. Roy moves back and plays it with gentle hands. It takes the inner half and runs behind square leg for a run.
A little bit of movement. Hazlewood lands it on a length close to leg, Burns tries to flick but there is some extra bounce. It beats Rory's bat and strikes him on the back thigh.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks in time to let that one go over him.
Shortish and on off, blocked off the back foot by Burns.
Fullish and on middle, Burns gets forward a bit and pushes it down to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Roy defends it off his back foot to the off side.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Jason blocks it from the back foot. He is trying to play nice and late. But needs to watch out for the late movement.
Shortish and close to off, moving back in sharply, Roy shoulders arms and it heads over his off stump. Brave leave.

FOUR! Streaky! But the crowd loved it! Cummins spears in a fuller length ball on off, angling in and it straightens after pitching, Roy tries playing straight but ends up slicing it off the outside half through cover-point.
Hurls in a good length ball in the zone outside off, Jason makes a watchful leave much to the crowd's delight.
A length ball on off, Roy is on the front foot as he plays a confident drive. Finds the short cover fielder though.
Loopy and full on middle, it grips and spins a bit, Burns flicks it in front of square leg for a couple of runs.
Spin and bounce, it's short and outside off, Burns mistimes his back foot punch to covers.
Floated and full on middle, it's defended off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up delivery, full and on off, Burns defends it from the outer half of his bat.
Short delivery, outside off, Burns rocks back and slaps it to sweeper cover for a run.
Flighted delivery, landing full on middle, Jason eases it down through mid on for a single. Lunch on Day 3!
On a length and a hint of inward movement, Roy comes on the front foot and defends it off the inner half to the leg side.
On a length and around off, Roy defends with a strong forward defense.
Short of a length and coming in, Roy is in two minds as he fends that from within the crease and the ball takes the inside edge once again and goes to the leg side.

An appeal for a caught behind  but the umpire turns it down. Cummins bowls one on a length and gets some extra purchase too. The ball goes past the inside edge and on its way to the keeper after flicking the trousers. The Australian players appeal but the umpire says no.
On a length and on the pads, Roy flicks it past the square leg fielder for a couple.
Ohhh! Almost a replica of the first innings dismissal. Roy goes fetching for the ball which is way outside off but luckily does not connect and the ball goes past the outside edge.
On a length and around off, Burns is solid as he defends it off his back foot.
Length ball outside off, Burns defends by coming right behind the line of the delivery.
Short and outside off, Burns ducks under it comfortably.
Burns now makes the mistake of playing the ball outside off. But luckily for him, the ball does not shave the wood on its way to the keeper.
Fullish and outside off, Burns drives it through point for a couple of runs.

OUT! Caught at first slip! Hazlewood draws first blood with an exceptional delivery! Back of a length ball on middle and off, nipping away after landing, Burns sticks back to defend but it takes the outer edge of his willow and flies straight into the hands of Warner. David in no mood to drop anything coming his way in this Test match, fifth grab for him. Big blow to England as their in-form batsman is sent packing early.
On a length and around off, Roy punches it to point off the outside half of his bat.
On a length and on off, Roy is on the front foot to defend.

OUT! Stumps shattered! Roy's misery in plain clothes continues. England in early trouble yet again. Cummins is the bowler this time. He makes full use of the lack of footwork from Jason Roy. Excellent delivery, on a fuller length, straighter in line and nipping away just enough to beat Roy's defense. It whizzes past the outside edge and cannons onto the stumps. Jason trudges back.

STREAKY FOUR! Nervy beginning for Denly. Cummins lands it on a length close to the off stump line and gets it to move away just a shade. A moment of indecision there from Denly as he decides late to make a leave. But before he could withdraw his bat, it has taken the bottom edge and sped right through the slip cordon for a boundary behind. Denly is off the mark in a lucky manner.
Bouncer this time! But the line is down the leg side and hence it's an easy leave for the new batsman.
Shortish ball around middle and off, Denly defends it from the back foot. End of a successful over from Cummins.
On a length and around off, Root is late in bringing his bat down but defends it within the crease at the last moment.
Play and a miss. It's quite evident that Root is struggling for runs. He gets sucked into this length ball outside off, but cannot lay bat on it.
Length ball and outside off, Root defends it with the full face of the bat.

Short in length and outside off, Root slashes his bat at it and places his shot at backward point. The fielder there gets some hand on it and hence the ball slows down before the fence. The batsmen take three.
Length ball outside off, Denly looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

Overpitched and driven straight down the ground. Hazlewood goes full and Denly displays a straight bat to drive it past the mid off fielder. The fielder from mid off and mid on run and the former mops it up. Another three for England.
Back of a length ball around off, Denly pushes at it tamely but misses.
Hurls in a length delivery again, this time outside off, Joe shoulders arms.
Beaten! Peach of a delivery. Cummins gets a length ball to angle into the batsman around off, Denly is forced forward in defense but it nips away ever so slightly to beat the outside edge.
Short in length and wide outside off, an easy leave this time.
Bouncer around leg, Denly ducks underneath it.
Lands it close to the off stump and it shapes back in, Joe keeps his weight on the back leg and defends it safely.
On a length and around off, Root goes deep in his crease as he gets it off the inner half to mid-wicket for a single.
Length and outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Driven through the covers by the batsman.
A bouncer on middle, Denly ducks.
Beaten on the driver! Fuller in length and outside off, Denly decides to go for a big booming cover drive but is beaten as the ball straightens after landing.
Close to the off stump this time, on a length, Joe blocks it to the off side.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Puts it on a fuller length outside off, it's pushed through covers for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.

ON THE HELMET! This has happened for the third time today. A short ball outside off, Denly initially looks to duck but then he does not see the ball at all. He has got nowhere to go and just hopes that the cherry goes above him. Is hit bang on the helmet.
Excellent delivery, in the blockhole, outside off, watchfully dug out.
Around off, defended towards cover.

On a length outside off, Root looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Hazlewood appeals but the umpire shakes his head. The bowler is interested in the review but Matthew Wade at some close-in position, immediately shakes his head. Was there any wood involved? Yes. The first replay detects an inside edge onto his pads.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
A length ball outside off, another one cutting in, Root misses his tuck and is hit on the pads.
Outside off, let through to his counterpart.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
A length ball, around middle, Denly ducks. The ball does not bounce that much.

FOUR! Not too sure Denly was in total control of that shot. A length ball outside off, coming in, Joe looks to defend but is squared up as it moves away late. The ball takes the outside edge and flies through the vacant gully region to the third man fence.
A bumper, but down the leg side, Joe ducks.
Another one down the leg side, ducked under again.
That is a jaffa. On a length outside off, Joe looks to fend it off but the ball jabs back in and goes in between bat and pad, almost cutting him into half.
Another unimpressive bouncer, down the leg side.
Full and outside off, Root looks to drive but there is no feet movement. A play and a miss.
Outside off, this time the skipper lets it be.

FOUR! Off the edge but Root need not be entirely unhappy. Full and outside off, the skipper looks to defend but the ball moves away at the last moment, takes the outside edge, goes along the ground and finds the gap between the slips and gully. Third man fence is the destination. The stand moves to 20.
Outside off, left alone.

A short ball outside off, Joe looks to pull but then bails out. Just a customary man in the deep on the leg side for Root, the fine leg. Probably that is why he thought about going after it initially.
Outside off, let through to the keeper again.

ANOTHER ONE DOES NOT BOUNCE. Joe Denly continues to be peppered with short stuff. Again, he takes his eyes off the ball, closing them and ducking ungainly. Gets hit on the left arm. Cummins appeals for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. He wants a review and Paine is interested but others advice him not to go for it as it looks high. Ball Tracker confirms. Going over the stumps. Denly has one thing in his favour for getting hit, if someone blames his technique. We have not seen too many balls misbehave, so indifferent bounce is slowly creeping into the equation now.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
A bouncer, outside off this time, ducked calmly once more.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
The crowd cheers as Denly gets a run. Outside off, coming in, Joe looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge towards mid on. A single taken.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Landed outside off, let through.
A length ball outside off, Joe pushes it towards cover and sets off for a non-existent single but is sensibly sent back by Joe Root.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around middle, pushed towards mid on.
A short ball outside off, Root hops and pushes it towards point.
Around off, defended solidly.
Back of a length outside off, blocked towards the bowler.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Outside off, on a length, moving away, guided straight to gully.
Around off, on a length, tucked through square leg for a single. Root moves to double figures with that.
Full and outside off, Root leans and drives it behind point. Travis Head dives full stretch to his left to stop it.
Around off, flicked behind square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Landed outside off, played off the back foot towards point.

FOUR! Nice, positive intent! Well, that came out of the blue. Full and outside off, Denly comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it cleanly over mid off. No power used, just simple placement.
Full and around off, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, defended solidly.
Around off, blocked solidly.
Back of a length outside off, watchfully blocked out.

FOUR! A bit of an outside edge but Root will take it. Outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball moves away, takes the outside edge, goes to ground and explores the gap between second slip and gully.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Outside off, tapped towards point for a single.
Landed outside off, Root gets back and across, looks to defend but then tries to withdraw his bat. The ball just zips past the outside edge.
Outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Root gets down and sweeps it through square leg for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, pushed towards mid on for a run.
Full and outside off, watchfully pushed back.

WIDE. A wild bouncer, down the leg side, Denly ducks. The umpire wides it and the crowd cheers. 50 UP FOR ENGLAND! They were 6 down when they touched this score yesterday, so the applause. 309 more to win.
Wide outside off, fuller in length, let through.
One more delivery in that play-and-try-to-gift-your-wicket channel, well outside off, Denly is not interested in being a Santa Clause.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Outside off, dabbed straight to gully.
Ahhh... the patience almost goes. Full and wide outside off, Denly looks to drive but misses. Pattinson smiles.

EDGED, OVER THE SLIP CORDON! A short ball, outside off, Denly looks to fend it off but suddenly, the ball rises, kicking off the seam, takes the top half of the bat and lobs over the slips! Three men run after it and manage to stop it before it touches the ropes. Two runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and outside off, swept through square leg for a single.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Outside off, played straight to point.
Another one down the leg side, flick shot missed again.
Outside off, on a length, Root looks to push it away from his body but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, Joe initially looks to play but then tries to withdraw his bat. Is beaten as he is late.
The batsman has been struck on the thigh-pad. They pick up a single. Leg bye given by the umpire.
Full snd outside off, Root pads it away. Khawaja and Paine appeal but then stay quiet. Did not quite come back in.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Full and outside off, tossed up slightly, driven straight to cover once again.
Outside off, Joe looks to play at that but misses.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on for a quick single.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Full and around off, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.

A length ball outside off, coming back in, Denly is caught in his crease as he looks to tuck but misses and is hit on the pads. Australia appeal for LBW but it is turned down. Ball Tracker shows it to be going over the top.
Outside off, played straight to point.

WIDE. A bit harsh on Patto. Banged on a length, it hits the deck and then shoots up well above the batsman's head. My colleague Nabu, watching the replays closely, comments, 'Gosh. That just kicked up way too high!' Yup, mate. Which is why Shane Warne also feels that the umpire was a bit too harsh.
A bouncer, this time not that high, Joe ducks.
Full and outside off, JD looks to drive but misses.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A short ball, outside off, Root looks to pull but the ball barely comes off the pitch. Takes the under edge and goes to short mid-wicket. Excellent contest going on.
Outside off, blocked from the crease.
Full and around off, watchfully kept out.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Goes back and gently nudges it through square leg for a single.

This guy is a machine. And he is bowling to another machine. Nice. Watching Transformers on a sports channel. This bloke has just come off some rest, wandering around somewhere at fine leg or third man but no looseners for him. First ball, in the avenue of apprehension. Makes Root play. Gets the ball to move away and beat the outside edge. Joshua smiles.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, let through once again.
Outside off, Joe looks to defend but the ball comes in, takes the inside edge and squirts to square leg. A single taken.
Outside off, let through to the keeper.

FOUR! SMASH! Shot of the innings. That says about England's confidence at the moment. Does not matter if you were 67 all out a day ago. Stay in the present. Make use of the presents as well. Hazlewood offers a Christmas gift, landing a half-tracker outside off and Denly pounces. Swivels and pulls it over mid-wicket. No one moves. Someone fetch that! Under 300 needed to win now.
Around off, coming in, Root misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, nicely blocked out.
Full and around middle, Root gets down and sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.

HOW CLOSE WAS THAT? Full and around middle, Denly comes forward and looks to flick. Gets it towards short leg. Marnus Labuschagne is late to react but the ball ricochets off his pads. Denly is out of his crease and has to hurry back but luckily for him, the ball misses the stumps!
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Around off, watchfully defended.

50-RUN STAND IS UP! It has taken more than 22 overs but it is okay. The message is clear - Do not allow the Aussies in. Tire the fast bowlers out, get the Labuschagnes and the Heads to bowl and then make the opposition's heads roll. Short and outside off, pulled through square leg for the single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and outside off, Denly looks to drive but the ball comes back in and beats the inside edge. Hazlewood feels it is time for some pre-tea chat. Denly is not too keen though.
Full and around off, worked through mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Around off, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Played to mid-wicket region by the batsman.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.

Soft edge and FOUR! Huge cheer from the English crowd as the home team goes past their first innings score. A length ball just outside off, Root pushes inside the line with a loose bottom hand and gets it away off the outside edge. It runs through the gap between gully and third slip for a boundary.
On a length and around off, Root hangs on the back foot in defense.
Back of a length ball on off, shaping in, Joe defends it from the crease.
Hazlewood serves it on a fuller length around middle, Root clips it towards mid-wicket where Head dives and parries it towards mid on. A single is stolen.
Extra movement and bounce off the surface. It's around off, Denly tries working it away but misses. He takes a hit on his thigh pad.

FOUR! Well played! A pitched up delivery close to off, Denly presses forward, opens the face of his bat, allows the ball to come to him and then quietly guides it past gully. Hazlewood is getting frustrated, lets out some words for the batsman.
Flatter and shorter delivery on middle, Root gets back and helps it past short leg to mid-wicket.
Once again the length is on the shorter side, Root moves back and defends it to the off side.
Quicker delivery, on middle, Joe remains on the back foot as he defends it down.
Fine delivery. Full and flighted just outside off, Root lunges to defend but it doesn't spin much and catches the inside edge. The ball races down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
A real drag down by Marnus this time. Root uses the depth of his crease and pulls it behind square leg for one.
Loopy and full outside off, Denly takes his front leg forward, covers the line and shoulders arms.
Angles in a full length ball on off, Root defends it towards covers and scampers across to the other end.
Lands it on a length and close to off stump, Denly pushes it out with an angled bat to point.
Full and on off, shaping back in, Denly presents the full face of the bat in defense.
Back of a length delivery on off, Denly stands back and pulls it through backward square leg. Cummins moves across to his left to stop the ball and interestingly, they take just a run.
Tap and run. Doing it with ease, England. Good length ball close to off, JR plays it with soft hands in front of point and steals a run.

Some movement there but the line is too straight and it's going down. Denly fails to flick and it goes off his pads to square leg. A leg bye to close the over, 4 coming off it. This partnership has now moved on to England's first innings score. 277 needed more for a win.
Lunges to defend but it takes the inside edge and rolls behind square leg for a run.
Tossed up ball landing full on off, Root is on the front foot in defense.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it with the spin through covers for one.
Labuschagne drags his length short on off, Denly goes back and punches it to sweeper cover for a run.
Quicker one, short and close to off, a late cut by Root finds short third man.

Another back foot square cut by Root and this time he manages to beat backward point. A couple of runs taken. Things going on smoothly at the moment for the hosts. Devil's number for Australia is up on the scoreboard.
Inside edge. Good length ball on off, a hint of inward shape, Denly tries defending from the back foot but it takes the inner half of his blade and strikes him on the pads.
Hurls a good length ball again, this time the channel is outside off and it holds its line a bit, Denly shoulders arms.
Puts it a bit fuller this time, outside off, JD gets on the front foot and pushes it to short cover.

Fantastic take by Tim Paine! Cummins bends his back to dig in a short ball on middle, Denly ducks easily. Paine moves across to his left to collect the ball but it swirls away a bit to his right. Good reaction shown by the Aussie skipper to stick it in his right hand.
Fuller and on off, moving in a bit, Denly tries to play the off drive but it goes off the inner half to mid on.
Solid this time. Good length ball on off, Denly covers the line and blocks it right under his watchful eyes.
Labuschagne bowls a flatter leg spinner from 'round the wicket. It's on middle and defended from the back foot by Joe Root.
Tossed up ball on middle, Root turns it on the leg side from the crease but it goes on one bounce to Head at short leg.
Gets it past Head this time. Full and on middle, Root clips it through mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
Short and around leg, Root goes deep inside the crease with the pull shot but fails to connect. He gets hit on the thigh pad in the process.
Root has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Labuschagne gives it a good rip and bowls it full around off, Root leans forward and defends it cautiously.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks in time to let that one go over him.

UPPISHHHHH! Safe... Heart in mouth stuff for Joe Denly. Cummins dishes out a back of a length ball on middle and leg and it zips off the surface. Denly is caught in a tangle as he attempts to fend it away. But the ball climbs to gather the splice of his bat and loops in the air. It falls safely behind square leg as Head charges across to his right from mid-wicket. Joe survives a nervy moment.
Fullish and on middle, Denly drives it back beautifully past his partner and mid on mops it up. One Joe wanted a single but the senior Joe turned it down.
A delivery around off, Denly pushes it out from the crease to cover-point where Lyon makes a fine stop
Bouncer. Ducked. But with a poor technique. He has his bat hanging like a periscope as he crouches. Archer got out doing the same in the first innings.
Denly has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Root has played it to the point region. One run added to the total.

Shout for a bat-pad! Not given and no DRS taken. A leg spinner landing outside leg, Denly offers no shot and takes it on the pads. It deflects then onto his waists and lobs up. Wade catches it in the second attempt as he goes down. No appeal from him but Paine is excited. The umpire stays put and since Wade ain't sure, no technology is taken.
Full and floated on middle and off, Denly defends it off his front foot.
Tossed up ball landing outside leg, Denly pads it away safely.
Very full and outside off, it's pushed off the front foot to covers. That will be TEA ON DAY 3!
MISFIELD, FOUR! Sloppy start by Australia to the session. Full and outside off, Root leans and drives it through the covers. Marcus Harris dives over the ball and it goes through.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Around off, tucked through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Denly gets a big stride forward and lets it through.
Outside off, Joe looks to defend but the ball hits the bat, then sneaks between the legs and goes to short leg.
Outside off again, JD smothers the spin watchfully.
A length ball outside off, Root plays inside the line and is beaten.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.

Huge, huge shout from Pattinson. Chats for a review. Thoughts ponder. Eventually, with 2 seconds left, the idea is dropped. A length ball outside off, coming in sharply, Root looked to defend but got hit on the pads. It seemed like the ball hit the pad first, but then, thoughts of an inside edge arose as well. Replays show that it was pad first but the impact was outside off.
Full and outside off, watchfully driven back. Stopped by the bowler.
Around off, tight, compact defense from Root.

FOUR BYES! That is a grubber. Nothing a batsman can do about that. Or the keeper. Full and outside off, Denly goes right back to defend but the ball shoots low and goes beneath the bat. Paine tries to close his legs and stop that but the ball goes through.
Outside off, left alone.
Pushes this towards long on for a single to raise huge cheers from the crowd. 100 UP FOR ENGLAND.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Joe looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. An LBW appeal ensues but the impact is outside off.
Full and outside off, swept fine for a single.
Outside off, solidly defended.

A jaffa. The Aussies are getting frustrated. They are bowling well but not getting the edges. This one pitches outside off and then straightens a touch. Root tries his best to defend but the ball scoots past the outside edge.

Outside off, dabbed straight to gully. 'That is a one-day shot,' chides Nasser Hussain on air. Yes, that shot can be avoided in this format. Especially with people waiting for you to play that and nick one.
Outside off, defended to the leg side.
Full and around off, driven straight back. Pattinson flings himself to his right and parries it towards mid on.
Strays down the leg side, tucked through fine leg for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Pushes this straight to point.
Full and outside off, pushed towards mid on.
Full and around off, Root comes down the track and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! 'ROOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOT!' cheers the crowd. Ben Stokes stands up and applauds in the dressing room. Oh, the run machine is back. Two ducks on the bounce, but a hat-trick is avoided and how. Half century for Joe Root, so far so good but the battle is half done. Time for another 50 at least. Full and outside off, Root drives this through the covers and gets the boundary. Raises his bat to acknowledge the applause.
FOUR! Down the leg side, Root goes back and gently tickles it to the fine leg fence. The fielder is a bit square and cannot get there! 249 more to win now.

FOUR! Sublime! This time from the bat of Joe Denly. Pattinson delivers it on a length outside off, Joe strides forward and delightfully strokes it through covers. Three fours on the bounce and England are on the charge!

100-run stand comes up and the English crowd has gone bonkers! They are just loving this fightback. A delivery angling down the leg side, Denly eases it fine down the leg side for one. Slowly but steadily, England are pushing Australia in a corner with this partnership.
Back of a length ball on off, Root sticks on the back foot and taps it down to point.
Hurls a good length delivery in the zone outside off, Root covers his stumps and leaves it easily.

Misfield at gully! Shortish and just outside off, Root plays it nice and late to tap it towards Khawaja. He gets down to stop it but there is some uneven bounce. The ball gets deflected behind and the batsmen take a run.
Nice use of the wrists this time as Denly works it through mid-wicket for a run.
Starts with a gentle loosener in the channel wide outside off, Denly has nothing to do with it.
Puts it on a full length around off, a hint of inward shape there, Denly lunges to drive but it takes the inner half and rolls to mid on.
Aerial bit safe! Back of a length ball on middle, Denly glances it across the line, it's uppish but drops short of mid-wicket.
Fullish and outside off, Denly leans forward and pushes it with soft hands at covers for one. All too easy at the moment. Australia need to step up their intensity in the field.
Shortish and on off, angling in, Root allows the ball to meet his bat and taps it down late towards gully.
Cummins goes short with his length and darts it on off, Root offers a solid back foot defense.
Too full and too straight, Denly covers the angle and pushes it to mid on.
Effort ball. Pattinson lets out a grunt and hurls in a short ball around leg, Denly ducks with ease.
Just a touch short in length on off, Denly goes on his toes and turns it in the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
Drops it on a length and just outside off, Root strides forward and pushes it with soft hands to covers.

Nicely played but not in the gap. Pattinson dishes out a length delivery in the zone outside off, Root takes a big stride forward and strokes it with nice timing square of the wicket on the off side. It goes straight to point.
Closer to off stump, on a good length, the English skipper plays it down from the back foot. It takes the outer half and rolls to point again.
Fuller length ball angling in around off, Denly is on the front foot as he pushes it from the middle of the bat to mid on.
Good leave. On a length and just outside off, shaping in just a hint, Denly covers his stumps and allows it through.
Very full and spearing in on off, Denly has his bat down in time as he keeps it out safely to mid on.
Cummins tries to tempt Denly into a drive but Joe keeps his patience and makes a leave. Pat smiles.
Shortish ball on middle, rising onto the batsman, Denly gets back and nudges it to fine leg for a run.
Around off, on a full length, Root defends it from the middle of his bat.
Too full in length and on off, Denly drives it confidently but finds the mid off fielder.
Another delivery angling into the batsman, Denly is forward in defense and keeps it out from the outer half of his bat.
Grunts and bowls. Shortish and on top of off, easily defended off the back foot by Denly.
Lands it on a length and outside off, going straight on, Denly shoulders arms.
Presses forward to a full ball moving back into him and then pushes it back to the bowler off the inner half of his blade.
Extra bounce on this occasion. On a good length around middle and leg, Denly fails to work it away on the leg side and it deflects off his pads to backward point. A leg bye picked.
Good length delivery in the corridor outside off, Denly watches the line closely before leaving it.
Picks the line of the length delivery is outside off and Denly takes his bat far away from the ball. Easy leave.
Shortish on middle and leg, Denly tries flicking but misses. It brushes his pads and goes to fine leg for a leg bye.
Back of a length ball on middle, Root helps it through the gap between backward square leg and short leg for one.
Short in length again, around middle and leg, Denly plays a nicely controlled glance wide of short backward square leg for a run.
Cummins digs in another short delivery, this time it's outside off, Root hooks it across the line, rolls his wrists over the shot and keeps it all along the ground through square leg for a single.
Fuller in length on off, angling in, Root gets forward and defends it back to the bowler.
This one stays low after moving back into the batsman from a length outside off. Root does well to keep his eyes on the ball till the last second as he defends it towards mid on by going down low.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
A touch short and outside off, at 86 mph, Root plays it late and tries to guide it wide of the slip cordon but the third slip fielder dives across to his right to make the stop.
Keeps his line on the middle stump line and Root defends it back by staying inside the crease.
Clocks 86.9 mph and delivers it around off, Root blocks again from the crease. Tidy stuff from Josh, a maiden to start his new spell.
Bouncer around leg, sliding down, Denly easily ducks underneath it.
